| ‚ùì Question                                                           | üí¨ Answer                                                                      |
| -------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Q1. What is Huffman coding?                                          | A lossless data compression algorithm based on character frequencies.          |
| Q2. What is the main idea behind Huffman Coding?                     | Assign shorter binary codes to frequent symbols and longer codes to rare ones. |
| Q3. What type of algorithm is it?                                    | Greedy algorithm.                                                              |
| Q4. What data structure is used?                                     | Min Heap (Priority Queue).                                                     |
| Q5. What does each node in Huffman Tree represent?                   | A character (leaf node) or combined frequency (internal node).                 |
| Q6. What is the time complexity?                                     | O(n log n)                                                                     |
| Q7. What is the space complexity?                                    | O(n)                                                                           |
| Q8. What is the output of Huffman coding?                            | A set of variable-length binary codes for each symbol.                         |
| Q9. What are real-world applications?                                | File compression (ZIP), image compression (JPEG), video (MPEG).                |
| Q10. Why is Huffman Coding called lossless?                          | Because no data is lost during compression or decompression.                   |
| Q11. What is the difference between Huffman and Run-Length Encoding? | Huffman uses frequency-based binary tree; RLE counts consecutive symbols.      |
| Q12. Can two characters have the same code?                          | No, Huffman codes are prefix-free ‚Äî no code is a prefix of another.            |




| Concept             | Description                                                |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| Algorithm Type      | Greedy Algorithm                                           |
| Goal                | Compress data by minimizing average code length            |
| Data Structure Used | Binary Tree + Min Heap                                     |
| Principle           | Combine two smallest frequencies repeatedly                |
| Encoding Rule       | Left ‚Üí ‚Äò0‚Äô, Right ‚Üí ‚Äò1‚Äô                                    |
| Application         | Text compression, data transmission (e.g., ZIP, JPEG, MP3) |



| Type         | Description                      | Complexity     |
| ------------ | -------------------------------- | -------------- |
| ‚è±Ô∏è **Time**  | Building Huffman Tree using heap | **O(n log n)** |
