Huffman Coding Algorithm

Huffman coding is a Greedy Algorithm used for data compression.
It builds a binary tree where each leaf node represents a symbol and its frequency.
The two smallest frequencies are combined iteratively until one root remains.
Codes are assigned: Left ‚Üí 0, Right ‚Üí 1.
The algorithm minimizes the total number of bits required.

Complexity:
Time = O(n log n), Space = O(n)
